# .assetsignore — files that must NOT be published as public static assets on sovenn.app.
# Cloudflare Workers Static Assets reads this from the assets directory root (assets.directory = ".").
# Syntax is .gitignore-style. This protects EVERY deploy path (git pipeline, `wrangler deploy`,
# manual upload) from serving source, config, internal docs, or local junk.

# --- Version control & deploy config (never serve) ---
.git
.gitignore
.assetsignore
wrangler.jsonc
.wrangler
# ^ wrangler creates .wrangler/ (cache/wrangler-account.json, tmp/) in the CWD during
#   `wrangler login`/`deploy`. With assets.directory = ".", it MUST be excluded or the
#   account id + email get served publicly.

# --- Secrets & user data (MUST NOT ever be served publicly) ---
# A local .env/.dev.vars (holds the worker's GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET) or a user's exported
# contacts backup left in the working tree during a manual `wrangler deploy` would
# otherwise be fetchable at sovenn.app/<file> — the same leak class as the .wrangler
# incident. These mirror .gitignore, but WITHOUT its `!*.example` negations: in
# .assetsignore a negation means "publish it", so we deliberately exclude even the
# examples from being served.
.env*
.dev.vars*
*.kith
kith-backup*.json

# --- CI / docs / server / tests: source, not for the browser ---
.github
worker
tooling
README.md
RELEASE-CHECKLIST.md

# --- Private / internal: never publish ---
Sovenn-Internal
*.pdf
*.mp4

# --- Local build junk (belt-and-suspenders; mostly untracked) ---
node_modules
*.log
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
